Title: Virasoro Singular Vectors via Quantum DS Reduction

Authors: A.Ch. Ganchev and V.B. Petkova

Comments: 7 pages, plain TeX, SISSA-74/93/EP

Journal-ref: Phys. Lett. B318 (1993) 77-84

The BRST quantisation of the Drinfeld - Sokolov reduction is exploited torecover all singular vectors of the Virasoro algebra Verma modules from thecorresponding $A^{(1)}_1\,$ ones. The two types of singular vectors are shownto be identical modulo terms trivial in the $Q_{BRST}$ cohomology. The maintool is a quantum version of the DS gauge transformation.